OL,6,FBetween 1949 and the mid-1970s, an
OL,7,Festimated 200,000 women were sent away
OL,8,Fto mother and baby homes run by
OL,9,Fchurches and the state where babies
OL,10,Fwere put up for adoption or died
OL,11,Fthrough poor care.
OL,13,FAn ITV News' investigation has found
OL,14,Faccounts of cruelty and abuse inside
OL,15,Fseveral institutions.
OL,17,FSt Monica's maternity home in Kendal,
OL,18,Fwhich was run by the Church of
OL,19,FEngland's Diocese of Carlisle until
OL,20,Fits closure in 1970, has a dark
OL,21,Fhistory.
